        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 5:08PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 508 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles southeast of Hiawassee to 9 miles
south of Clayton. Movement was southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarkesville, Tiger, Tallulah Falls, Lake Rabun, Lake Burton,
Lakemont, Tallulah Gorge State Park, Hollywood, Batesville, and Seed
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
